=head1 DESCRIPTION

The drift status summary of the landing zone.

If the landing zone differs from the expected configuration, it is
defined to be in a state of drift. You can repair this drift by
resetting the landing zone.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Status => Str

The drift status of the landing zone.

Valid values:

=over

=item *

C<DRIFTED>: The landing zone deployed in this configuration does not
match the configuration that Amazon Web Services Control Tower
expected.

=item *

C<IN_SYNC>: The landing zone deployed in this configuration matches the
configuration that Amazon Web Services Control Tower expected.

=back




